   <head>Quaere. 1.</head>
   <p n="1">1. If a man upon probability affirme such a poynt, or out of ignorance &amp; mistake, conclude it
<pb facs="24"/>
certaine, &amp; so relate it, as by him conceaved, doth he hereby neces<g ref="char:EOLhyphen"/>sarily manifest a spirit of con<g ref="char:EOLhyphen"/>tradiction, or the weaknes of his owne apprehension?</p>
   <p n="2">2. If charity hopes the best, that can be conceaved in reason, to iudge mens spirits by grounds weake, &amp; feeble, out of which nothing can be concluded.</p>
   <p>Quaere, whether it be not uncharitable censuring?</p>
   <p n="3">3. Do all those who contradict the like conceites of the Rej: as false, manifest a sinful spirit in lusting after contradiction?</p>
</div>
